value.value: Caudal fin lepidotrichium located upon or above the notochord.
Posteriorly projecting bony tubercle that is located proximal to the lateral condyle of the femur.
A small plate of cartilage synchondrotically united with the pubis. Modified from Baez and Harrison 2005.
The vertical plate of bone or cartilage attached to the median line of the sternum. Modified from Baumel et al. 1993.

definition.value: An enlarged ossified keel is found in most, but not all,  volant birds.

value.value: Fin spine that is part of a median fin.
A spine that is part of some fin.
An opening in the dermal armour of basal gnathostomes that encloses the pectoral fins. (modified from Young 2010).
A notch for the articulation of the clavicle on other girdle elements.
Posteriordorsal process of the ilium.

definition.value: It spresences gives the ilium a  'double headed' appearence.

value.value: A bony projection on the lateral side of the tibia, allowing contact between the later and the fibula.
Zone of bone organ located on the flat ventral side of the distal region of the furcula, serving as attachment region for pectoral muscles.
Centrale in the postaxial region of the mesopodium.

definition.value: The paried limbs have a main axis running proximodistally trough the stylopodiam element (humerus/femur). from the zeugopodium distally elements can be divided into preaxial (on the radius/tibia side) and postaxial (ulna/fibula) sides. The exact orientation of these axises vary depending on the orientation of the limb in a neutral position.

value.value: Centrale in the preaxial side of the mesopodium.

definition.value: The paried limbs have a main axis running proximodistally trough the stylopodiam element (humerus/femur). from the zeugopodium distally elements can be divided into preaxial (on the radius/tibia side) and postaxial (ulna/fibula) sides. The exact orientation of these axises vary depending on the orientation of the limb in a neutral position.

value.value: A constricted region of the ilium which is dorsal to the acetabulular region. Prior to the expansion of the iliac blade.
Bony projection that is part of the dorsal surface of the ischim, where it articulates with the ilium.
Bony projection that is part of the dorsal surface of the pubis where it meets the ilium.
Articular surface on calcaneum for the fibula.
Articular surface on the astragalus for the fibula.
Region consisitng of the ethmoid and sphenoid bones.
Eminence on the proximo-dorsal surface of the ungual, for attachment of flexor muscles.
The medial most digit of the manus skeleton.

definition.value: In most taxa this is digits II-IV, but this varies based on the number of digits and thier identity in the taxa examined.

value.value: Process on infraspinous (region below the spine) of scapula.
The deep fossa between the femoral condyles in which the cruciate ligaments are attached. From Medilexicon.com.
Spine ventrally located on the body and not part of the pectoral, pelvic or anal fins.
Expansion of the distal region of the ischium.
The most lateral of the paired series of extrascapular bones and is the bone where the intersection of the otic, postotic and extrascapular or supratemporal canals occur.
A bony process on the dorsal side of the proximal region of the humerus which corresponds to the insertion site of the Latissimus dorsi muscle.
Muscle that represents one branch of the larger triceps brachii, origination site near the glenoid fossa on the scapula.
Dermal armour plate that is situated behind the head and constitute the dorsal most portion of the dermal shoulder girdle. Modified from Brazeau 2009, Young 2010.
The medial of the the paired series of extrascapular bones which carries the extrascapular or supratemporal canal.
Pits located on the proximodorsal part of metacarpals denoting the attachemnt sites for ligaments.
Opening and/or passageway for nerve(s) in bone.
A distinct region on a skeletal element that demarcates the attachment area of a muscle or tendon. Often associated with rugosity or tubercles.

definition.value: While this term is applicable to both vertebrates and invertebrates, the qualities used to demarcate muscle attachment areas between the two groups may not be identical.

value.value: Process located on the ventral shaft of the ischium that denotes the attachment site of the pubio-ischio-femoralis externus.

definition.value: In birds the pubio-ischio-femoralis externus is sometimes called the M.oburatorius lateralis and medialis.

value.value: The flanking digit of the manus.

definition.value: In most taxa this is digits I and V, but this varies based on the number of digits in the manus

value.value: The flanking digit of the pes.

definition.value: In most taxa this is digits I and V, but this varies based on the number of digits in the pes.

value.value: Spine located anterior to the pectoral fin.
Spine located anterior to the pelvic fin and posterior to the pectoral fin.
A triangular, anteroventrally facing area developed between the preaxial margin of the humerus and the proximal limb of the ventral humeral ridge. Based on Callier et al. 2009 .
Elongate process forming the anteriormost part of the pubis.
An skeletal element of the upper pectoral girdle overlapped by the opercular and posttemporal bones.
Slender bone connected to the carpus in pterosaurs. The bone, which may have pointed forward, supports the propatagium, a membrane located between the carpus and pectoral region.

definition.value: This structure is unique to pterosaurs. There is debate wherther this structure is derived from metacarpal I, the carpal bones or is a a novel bone. See Unwin et al. 1996

value.value: Anteroposterior expansion of the distal region of the pubis.
Bony projection on the anterior portion of the ilium, anterior to the acetabulum that articulates with the pubis.
Contact zone between the pubis and the ischium.
A broad expnase of bone incorperating both the pubis and the ischium. Origin site for ventral limb muscle including the pubioishciofemoralis externus. Modified from Romer 1956 .
A muscle that originates from the puboischaidic plate and inserts on the tibia. Acts to adduct the hindlimb. Is anterior to cloacal gland in males. Modified from De luliis and Pulera.
Originates in on the pubic cartillage and inserts on the tibia, acts to adduct the hindlimb. Modified from De luliis and Pulera.
